Is this you? 👉🏽 “I dream of being a professional actor, and I hear people talking about what it’s like and that it’s important to keep a positive attitude… but what if I’m nowhere near being in the position to feel positive because I seem so far away from my dream?” 
I hear you. I’ve been there. And I’m still experiencing those thoughts sometimes. But now, I know better than to stay stuck there… 👇🏽👀

Something I’ve learned over 15 years of experiencing this life is that things can change, and FAST.

One day I feel like I will never work again, and the next I book a big contract that fills me with joy and hope and satisfaction that my dream is taking form. 🎬❤️‍🔥

The one thing that we know FOR SURE, is that everything is always changing. Literally, non stop, always, even the particles that make up our “physical “ body (in quotes because it is known now that we are made up of 99.9999% empty space a.k.a. energy in motion). 

So if everything is always changing, can it not change into what you want just as much as change into what you don’t want? Yes. Duh.

So now that we’ve established that, how can we keep heading towards what we DO want? Well, it’s building a strong foundation, a mindset, not just an attitude, but a “infinite possibilities” mindset, it’s more than a positive attitude, it’s a way of life. Reprogramming your mind to a state of abundance growth mindset that will always keep you looking ahead knowing that life is always bringing you everything you need to achieve your goals.

You just gotta help it out a little and hang out in the higher frequencies of positive expectation. 

That was today’s tip! Stay with me to get even more in the next few weeks as I’m about to announce something really cool that will help you do just that. Save this post for inspiration and motivation, share it to someone who might like it. Comment what you love about it. Talk to you later 🥰

How to find an acting agent? 👇🏽👇🏽👇🏽

Here’s my tip on taking the first steps:

Google the different acting Unions in your area (ex: ACTRA in Canada, SAG-AFTRA in the US, etc..)

Go to their resource page, or contact them to get a list of the legit agencies in your area.

Make a list of your top 3 agencies you feel drawn to. 

Prepare an professional acting package with your headshots, resume, demo and a letter of intent describing who you are and what your goals are.

Personalize your letter/package for each agent, remember, you are creating a long term relationship with your agent, so approach it that way. 

If you don’t get the response you’d like it’s all good, you are planting seeds that will grow into something in the long run. 

You are looking for someone who is right for you, someone who will be your ally, it’s about how you vibe with them. 

Prepare some questions for the first meeting you have with them. Go on your first date. And begin your new journey.

Yesterday I was doing my bi-monthly insta live for my subscribers. I opened my journal and read through my 3month goals/desires that I wrote three months ago. I noticed that naturally, I had manifested the thing on the list that I really desired which was to create 14 new songs (I’m well past that already) but that other things that I thought I wanted were not fully realized yet, or weren’t really on their way to it. Does that mean I am not going to experience or have those things? No, it just gives me more clarity and info about what I can do or adjust in my behaviours, actions and beliefs to meet the “frequency” of those desires so that they can express through me in the physical.

Today I started “It’s Already Yours” by one of my faves @manifestationbabe 💓 I took in that 95% of what we experience in our lives is dictated by our unconscious mind. That’s huge. That means that what occurs in our lives is mostly automatic patterns that were programmed into us when we were kids. 

The same automatic system that makes our hearts beat and keeps us alive. The unconscious mind is in charge of our survival. 

This means that even if the 5% of me who feels like “All My Dreams Can Come True!!!!” there’s still the 95% of me, which apparently got programmed by the age of 7 (yikes indeed), who is making sure that I don’t die. There is a part of myself for who change = death. 😳

LUCKILY this can be reprogrammed! Another coach of mine is making me go through a neuro-plasticity process that is doing the reprogramming. I learned that it is normal to meet resistance when reprogramming the brain. That’s why persistence and repetition over a period of time is super important, to sort of “break through” that protective gateway. Cus remember: survival? Change = bad = fear = death. 

That’s why affirmations don’t always work, because there’s a part of your mind that automatically rejects change. Which is which? I’m still discovering that.

But I’m in. And I’m excited for the new life I’m creating. And I’m grateful for the person I’m becoming.

4 years ago to the day, I took a leap of faith and launched myself into the music industry. It was always my plan, but the world didn’t know. 

 #InstaStory was my first release on June 9th 2019 (produced by @dln09 - happy bday🦋). 

My artist debut was welcomed by some and awkwardly received by others. 

At that time, I didn’t know how I was going to do it. So i took classes and red books about self publishing. 

And I dropped this song, and I was terrified, of being judged, of failing, of being an imposter (imposter syndrome can be destroyed!!! It’s a waste of time. You are not an imposter, you are NEW at something) as I realized I was not anywhere near the music industry. In acting I was “somebody” and in music i was a “nobody”. And many did not shy away from letting me know. Sometimes even in my own surroundings. 

It was humbling and also exhilarating, because I had a new dream to manifest. 💪🏽 

I actually cried and felt discouraged the day of my release. I felt like I had failed and nobody cared. 

I stuck with it. I kept the vision. 

I found allies along the way. I discovered a whole new world full of artists and music lovers. 

Within two years I was on the radio in the top 50, we got into the Canadian Billboard. After three years I started to be taken more seriously. And it is still taking shape. 

I spent all this past year creating new music with some epic people and it’s about to start flooding out. 

And the dream becomes reality as the days go by.

Happy bday to Insta Story — the OG single.

With love

The point here is to CONNECT with and FEEL GOOD IN our bodies, not to look perfect and fit.
